WEBVTT

00:06.300 --> 00:07.530
Oh, hey, Alan.

00:07.600 --> 00:09.560
Jake, your dad's here.

00:10.630 --> 00:12.230
So, how's it going?

00:12.300 --> 00:13.560
All good.

00:13.630 --> 00:14.960
Good.

00:15.030 --> 00:16.530
You?
Good.

00:16.600 --> 00:18.260
Well, good.

00:18.800 --> 00:21.260
Yeah, good.

00:24.560 --> 00:26.560
Gooood.

00:29.900 --> 00:32.229
Well, I, uh, I see you
put in a new mailbox.

00:32.299 --> 00:34.500
Oh, yeah, the old one
was pretty shoddy.

00:34.560 --> 00:36.960
Whoever put it in didn't
anchor the pole correctly.

00:37.030 --> 00:39.060
That would be me.

00:39.130 --> 00:40.760
Oh, sorry.

00:40.830 --> 00:42.900
The mailman was complaining
about the wiggle.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.830
Herb, the mailman's a pothead.

00:44.900 --> 00:47.630
Yeah, I know. I caught him
eating my tomato plants.

00:47.700 --> 00:50.130
Anyway, I just decided
to replace the whole thing.

00:50.200 --> 00:52.930
Yeah, I see it, uh,
it now says "The Melnicks."

00:53.000 --> 00:55.100
Well, I paid for the mailbox.

00:56.560 --> 00:58.130
I get my mail there.

00:58.200 --> 00:59.460
My name's Melnick...

00:59.530 --> 01:00.460
Yeah, I... I get it.

01:00.530 --> 01:02.500
I mean, what does it
say on your mailbox?

01:02.560 --> 01:04.500
Charlie Harper.

01:04.560 --> 01:06.500
Oh.

01:06.560 --> 01:08.930
Jake!

01:09.000 --> 01:11.800
No need to yell.
He's in the bathroom.

01:11.860 --> 01:13.400
Big surprise, eh?

01:13.460 --> 01:15.830
He's either shoveling it in
or shooting it out.

01:15.900 --> 01:20.060
Yeah, he's a regular Play-Doh
fun factory.

01:20.130 --> 01:22.430
Just go make sure he hasn't
fallen asleep in there again.

01:22.500 --> 01:23.500
Yes, dear.

01:25.230 --> 01:27.300
So, how's everything?

01:27.360 --> 01:28.960
Fine.

01:29.030 --> 01:31.730
Listen, Alan, I've been thinking
now that Jake's a teenager,

01:31.800 --> 01:34.100
he'd benefit from spending
some more time with his dad.

01:34.160 --> 01:36.030
Oh, oh, that would be great.

01:36.100 --> 01:37.360
Nothing would make me happier

01:37.430 --> 01:38.930
than to spending more time
with my son.

01:39.000 --> 01:40.600
Good.

01:40.660 --> 01:41.530
Hey, Dad.

01:41.600 --> 01:42.530
Oh, hey, buddy.

01:42.600 --> 01:43.560
All finished
in the bathroom?

01:43.630 --> 01:44.730
For now.

01:44.800 --> 01:46.200
You should've
seen the last one.

01:46.260 --> 01:47.860
It looked like
a question mark.

01:50.260 --> 01:51.200
Terrific.

01:51.260 --> 01:52.930
And it came out of my colon.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.030
Get it?

01:54.100 --> 01:55.300
Hilarious.

01:55.360 --> 01:56.360
Commas are easy.

01:56.430 --> 01:57.930
Go.

01:59.260 --> 02:03.130
Um, so, uh, what are we
talking about here?

02:03.200 --> 02:04.860
You know, an extra day or two
every other week?

02:04.930 --> 02:07.130
Actually, I was thinking more
like a solid three months.

02:07.200 --> 02:08.400
In a row?

02:08.460 --> 02:10.199
Alan, how many sons do you have?

02:10.259 --> 02:11.530
As many as you do.

02:11.600 --> 02:12.960
Look, do you want
your kid or not?

02:13.030 --> 02:16.560
Of course, but... well, I'll
have to clear it with Charlie,

02:16.630 --> 02:19.330
and... and there is
the financial issue.

02:19.400 --> 02:20.760
What financial issue?

02:20.830 --> 02:22.160
Well, if he's going
to be living with me,

02:22.230 --> 02:23.160
I'm thinking I should
get a sizeable break

02:23.230 --> 02:24.360
on the child support.

02:24.430 --> 02:26.260
Well, you're certainly entitled
to your opinion.

02:26.330 --> 02:27.300
Well, thank you.

