02:36.200 --> 02:38.030
Wait a minute.

02:39.760 --> 02:41.360
Three months in a row?!

02:41.430 --> 02:44.100
Come on.
It'll be fun.
For who?

02:44.160 --> 02:46.730
All he does is eat, sleep
and clog up the toilets.

02:46.800 --> 02:47.800
Shh!

02:47.860 --> 02:49.130
Let's talk
about this later.

02:49.200 --> 02:51.160
Oh, please, chowderhead
can't hear us.

02:51.230 --> 02:52.260
Right, chowderhead?

02:53.760 --> 02:55.030
See?

02:55.100 --> 02:58.130
Oh, just admit it:
you love having him around.

02:58.200 --> 03:01.800
I love having him around because
I always know he's leaving.

03:01.860 --> 03:04.960
Don't take the leaving part
away from me, Alan.

03:05.030 --> 03:06.600
Let's just give it a chance.

03:06.660 --> 03:07.830
See how it works.

03:07.900 --> 03:09.900
That's what Poland said
about the Germans.

03:09.960 --> 03:12.600
Been watching
the History Channel again?

03:12.660 --> 03:14.600
It's Nazi week.

03:14.660 --> 03:16.760
It's always Nazi week.

03:16.830 --> 03:18.160
Look, tell you what,

03:18.230 --> 03:20.260
why don't I take you and Jake
out to dinner tonight?

03:20.330 --> 03:22.330
Can we get chili burgers?

