03:57.260 --> 03:58.730
So, numbnuts...

04:01.600 --> 04:03.900
Any thoughts as to why your mom
dumped you off on us?

04:03.960 --> 04:05.000
Charlie.

04:05.060 --> 04:06.530
Oh, like you're not curious.

04:06.600 --> 04:08.530
No! No, I'm not curious.

04:08.600 --> 04:10.200
She just thought
it would be a good idea

04:10.260 --> 04:11.660
for him to spend more time
with his father.

04:11.730 --> 04:13.160
Yeah, and I'm trying
to save girls

04:13.230 --> 04:15.700
a long ride home on the freeway.

04:16.930 --> 04:19.500
So what's your theory, Alfalfa?

04:19.560 --> 04:21.329
I think you're just pretending
to be considerate

04:21.399 --> 04:22.900
so you can have sex with them.

04:27.160 --> 04:30.200
No, no, I mean
about your mother and Herb.

04:30.260 --> 04:31.200
Oh.

04:31.260 --> 04:32.530
They are fighting a lot.

04:32.600 --> 04:33.430
They're fighting?

04:33.500 --> 04:34.460
Yep.

04:34.530 --> 04:36.130
31.

04:37.100 --> 04:38.400
31?

04:38.460 --> 04:42.000
It's what you get when you add
24 and seven.

04:44.130 --> 04:46.600
You know, they're fighting
all the time.

04:46.660 --> 04:47.760
24/7.

04:47.830 --> 04:49.900
31.

04:49.960 --> 04:53.060
I'm not gonna make it
three months, Alan.

04:53.130 --> 04:54.030
You're gonna be fine.

04:54.100 --> 04:55.330
They're fighting
in front of you?

04:55.400 --> 04:56.960
They don't think
they're fighting in front of me

04:57.030 --> 04:58.400
'cause sometimes when
I wear the headphones,

04:58.460 --> 04:59.460
I turn the music off.

05:00.860 --> 05:02.600
And you figured that out
all by yourself?

05:02.660 --> 05:05.660
Hey, you may think I'm dumb,
but you overestimate me.

05:07.630 --> 05:10.230
My mistake.

05:10.300 --> 05:11.900
So what are they arguing about?

05:11.960 --> 05:13.900
Well, she doesn't
like his parents,

05:13.960 --> 05:15.930
he doesn't like her spending,
and something about sex.

05:16.000 --> 05:17.330
What about sex?

05:18.930 --> 05:21.430
That's when I turn the music
back on, you sick freak.

05:25.900 --> 05:26.960
Sorry.

05:27.030 --> 05:28.900
I mean, that's my mother.

05:28.960 --> 05:30.930
I said I'm sorry.

05:31.000 --> 05:33.630
Man, I'm not gonna make it
three months.

05:35.030 --> 05:38.330
<i>Oh, great, now he's got
the moral high ground.</i>

05:39.900 --> 05:41.200
Forget about that.

05:41.260 --> 05:42.700
The important thing is,

05:42.760 --> 05:46.530
Judith and Herb are having
marital problems.

05:46.600 --> 05:48.630
Why does that make you happy?

05:48.700 --> 05:50.560
Well, it's not happiness
exactly.

05:50.630 --> 05:51.700
It's just that, you know,

05:51.760 --> 05:53.330
<i>all these years
she's been blaming me</i>

05:53.400 --> 05:57.000
for the failure of our marriage,
and now...

05:57.060 --> 06:00.730
Yeah, I guess happiness
pretty much sums it up.

06:00.800 --> 06:02.960
* Men. *

06:04.360 --> 06:06.200
Hey, what's this I hear

06:06.260 --> 06:10.130
about Little Lord Skidmark
coming to live here full time?

06:10.200 --> 06:12.130
Oh, it's just for a few weeks.

06:12.200 --> 06:13.660
I'm sure
if we all pull together,

06:13.730 --> 06:15.200
you'll hardly even notice
he's here.

06:15.260 --> 06:17.230
Yeah, pull this.

06:18.930 --> 06:20.200
Charlie!

06:20.260 --> 06:22.930
You and me gotta
have a conversation.

06:25.360 --> 06:26.700
Nice talking to you.

06:27.930 --> 06:30.500
(doorbell rings)

06:30.560 --> 06:32.500
Hey, Alan.
Oh, hey, Herb.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.530
Judith asked me to drop
this stuff off for Jake.

06:34.600 --> 06:35.730
Oh, let me help you.

06:35.800 --> 06:38.730
Thanks.

06:38.800 --> 06:38.860
So, what have you two lovebirds
got planned

06:42.560 --> 06:43.830
for the next few months?

06:43.900 --> 06:45.800
Second honeymoon?

06:45.860 --> 06:47.300
No, not exactly.

06:47.360 --> 06:50.760
Hard to believe you're coming up
on your second anniversary.

06:50.830 --> 06:52.060
Yep. Hard to believe.

06:52.130 --> 06:54.430
Two years.

06:55.600 --> 06:57.730
Time flies
when you're having fun, eh?

06:57.800 --> 06:59.800
I wouldn't know.

07:01.560 --> 07:02.700
Hey, Herb.

07:02.760 --> 07:04.060
Hey, Charlie.

07:04.130 --> 07:06.930
You ask him about his marriage
going down the crapper?

07:10.560 --> 07:12.260
I was easing into it.

07:12.330 --> 07:14.360
So was I.

07:14.430 --> 07:15.760
What's the problem, Herb?

07:15.830 --> 07:17.130
Is it in the bedroom?

07:17.200 --> 07:18.930
It usually starts
in the bedroom.

07:19.000 --> 07:22.260
That's still my mother,
you sick freak!

07:22.330 --> 07:24.730
We usually wait till
he puts on headphones

07:24.800 --> 07:26.360
before we discuss
these things.

07:26.430 --> 07:28.760
Gee, Herb, something
you should know

07:28.830 --> 07:29.800
about the headphones is...

07:29.860 --> 07:32.430
Shh, shh!
Don't spoil it.

07:32.500 --> 07:34.430
So what's the deal?
Is it sex?

07:34.500 --> 07:36.930
No.

07:37.000 --> 07:39.630
Well, yeah, but...
it's no big deal.

07:39.700 --> 07:41.900
I mean every marriage
has an ebb and flow to it.

07:41.960 --> 07:43.260
Of course.
Sure. Sure.

07:43.330 --> 07:46.630
Right now Judith and I
are kind of ebbing.

07:46.700 --> 07:48.530
A lot.

07:48.600 --> 07:50.830
31.

07:52.360 --> 07:53.960
Right.

07:54.030 --> 07:56.130
31.

07:56.200 --> 07:57.460
I don't know
what's happening, man.

07:57.530 --> 07:59.130
We can't seem
to communicate anymore.

07:59.200 --> 08:00.960
She constantly
finds fault with me.

08:01.030 --> 08:02.160
I don't know
what to do.

08:02.230 --> 08:03.830
I'll tell you
what to do.

08:03.900 --> 08:07.630
What my testicle-challenged
brother should have done.

08:07.700 --> 08:09.260
As soon as
she starts complaining,

08:09.330 --> 08:10.400
you put your foot down.

08:10.460 --> 08:11.830
Let her know who's in charge.

08:11.900 --> 08:14.460
And no matter what, do not
let her use sex as a weapon.

08:14.530 --> 08:16.300
You let her know that if she
won't satisfy your needs,

08:16.360 --> 08:17.830
there's plenty of women
out there who will.

08:17.900 --> 08:18.630
Really?

08:18.700 --> 08:20.660
Why would I lie?

08:22.160 --> 08:26.000
Women like Judith respond to
strength and confidence, not...

08:26.060 --> 08:29.830
well, that.

08:29.900 --> 08:32.659
Oh, you make a compelling case.

08:32.730 --> 08:33.700
Damn right I do.

08:33.760 --> 08:35.200
Now go claim what's yours.

08:35.260 --> 08:36.960
I believe I will.

08:37.030 --> 08:38.030
Thanks, Charlie.

08:39.299 --> 08:41.299
I'm here for you, big guy.

08:43.159 --> 08:44.430
Why did you do that?

08:44.500 --> 08:46.430
I get bored.

08:50.330 --> 08:52.000
* Men. *

08:54.100 --> 08:56.100
Hey.
Hey.

08:58.430 --> 09:00.360
Why aren't you in school?

09:00.430 --> 09:01.700
I'm sick.

09:01.760 --> 09:03.730
Sick?

09:03.800 --> 09:07.060
Relax, I'm just faking
to get out of a math test.

09:07.130 --> 09:09.660
Oh, okay, good.

09:09.730 --> 09:11.130
You scared me.

09:11.200 --> 09:12.960
What's with the staple gun?

09:13.030 --> 09:15.630
Oh, the sole's coming
off my shoe.

09:16.630 --> 09:18.460
Ah.

09:18.530 --> 09:20.700
You might want
to take it off first.

09:22.360 --> 09:23.860
Good call.

09:30.830 --> 09:31.760
Morning.

09:31.830 --> 09:33.030
(staple gun clacking)

09:33.100 --> 09:34.900
It's none of my business,
but that's one kid

09:34.960 --> 09:38.430
who can't afford to miss
a single day of school.

09:38.500 --> 09:39.760
(staple gun clacking)

09:39.830 --> 09:43.830
Yeah, like school's
gonna make a difference.

09:45.060 --> 09:47.160
(staple gun clacking)
JAKE:
Ow! Crap!

09:48.630 --> 09:51.830
I stapled my fingers together.

09:51.900 --> 09:54.300
You got a point.

09:58.000 --> 10:00.430
* Men. *

10:00.500 --> 10:02.430
Come on, honey. Blow.

10:02.500 --> 10:03.830
(blowing nose)

10:08.060 --> 10:10.060
(muffled):
What's he got?

10:10.130 --> 10:12.030
A cold, I think.

10:12.100 --> 10:13.560
Then why didn't you
leave him at home?

10:14.830 --> 10:16.730
That way, we all don't
have to get sick.

10:16.800 --> 10:18.460
(coughing)

10:20.200 --> 10:21.760
And that's why
you should always
take your shoes

10:21.830 --> 10:22.930
to a fully qualified,
professional cobbler.

10:23.000 --> 10:26.900
You know what's good?
Apple cobbler.

10:26.960 --> 10:28.660
What's the damage, doc?

10:28.730 --> 10:31.430
Will he play
the violin again?

10:31.500 --> 10:32.700
He'll be fine.

10:32.760 --> 10:34.560
You might wanna keep him away
from staple guns.

10:34.630 --> 10:35.560
Right.

10:35.630 --> 10:37.130
Also nail guns,
glue guns,

10:37.200 --> 10:39.130
pretty much anything
with "gun" in it.

10:39.200 --> 10:41.560
Got it.
Thanks, Herb.

10:43.300 --> 10:45.100
Hey, Charlie, could I talk
for you a sec?

10:45.160 --> 10:47.100
Why don't you go wait
for me in the car?

10:47.160 --> 10:48.060
Gimme the keys.

10:48.130 --> 10:50.000
I'm not giving you the keys.

10:50.060 --> 10:51.500
Then how am I gonna wait
in the car?

10:51.560 --> 10:53.300
<i>Wait by the car.</i>

10:53.360 --> 10:56.260
I don't have sunscreen on.
I'm very fair-skinned.

10:56.330 --> 10:58.830
<i>Then wait under the car.</i>

11:02.000 --> 11:03.160
What's up?

11:03.230 --> 11:05.130
Well, remember that advice
you gave me

11:05.200 --> 11:06.460
about how
to handle Judith?

11:06.530 --> 11:08.900
Oh, gee, Herb,
that wasn't so much advice

11:08.960 --> 11:11.130
as, you know, social satire.

11:11.200 --> 11:12.960
Well, it worked
out great.

11:13.030 --> 11:14.160
Really?

11:14.230 --> 11:16.100
She bought
that king-of-the-castle crap?

11:16.160 --> 11:18.260
No, no, she kicked my ass out.

11:18.330 --> 11:20.130
But the thing is,
talking with you

11:20.200 --> 11:21.430
and seeing how you live,

11:21.500 --> 11:23.130
I'm convinced
I'm better off single.

11:23.200 --> 11:24.360
Is that so?

11:24.430 --> 11:26.760
Oh, yeah. I mean,
why chew on one chicken wing

11:26.830 --> 11:28.930
when you can eat
from the whole bucket?

11:29.000 --> 11:31.500
Just so there's no confusion.

11:31.560 --> 11:33.130
Chicken wings are...?

11:33.200 --> 11:34.800
Women, Charlie.

11:34.860 --> 11:36.330
I was offering up a metaphor.

11:36.400 --> 11:39.830
And you went with wings
rather than breasts and thighs.

11:39.900 --> 11:43.960
<i>Ooh, that is better.</i>

11:44.030 --> 11:46.630
Anyway, I was thinking maybe
you and I can go out sometime

11:46.700 --> 11:48.700
and get a party pack.

11:49.930 --> 11:51.360
Sex with strange women.

11:51.430 --> 11:53.300
I'm extending the metaphor.

11:53.360 --> 11:55.900
Of course.
Sure, let's do that sometime.

11:55.960 --> 11:58.030
Thanks again for
sewing up the kid.

11:58.100 --> 11:59.830
So, uh, what color
do you like?

11:59.900 --> 12:01.160
Excuse me?

12:03.530 --> 12:06.560
Oh, I-I was thinking Asian,
but I'll take the green.

12:08.300 --> 12:09.800
* Men. *

12:16.330 --> 12:17.260
Hey, Dad..

12:17.330 --> 12:18.200
Oh, hey.
How are you feeling?

12:18.260 --> 12:19.200
Fine.

12:19.260 --> 12:20.400
Throat's not sore anymore?

12:20.460 --> 12:24.260
(coughs)
Oh, yeah, a little.

12:24.330 --> 12:26.960
What happened to your fingers?

12:27.030 --> 12:29.430
Oh, I stapled 'em together.

12:31.900 --> 12:33.830
Ah.

12:33.900 --> 12:39.800
<i>Hey, hey, we do not leave
our shoes on the...</i>

12:44.630 --> 12:45.760
What the hell?

12:48.360 --> 12:53.030
We need to get rid
of the staple gun.

12:53.100 --> 12:55.830
Alan, staple guns don't staple
shoes to coffee tables.

12:55.900 --> 12:57.760
Idiots do.

12:59.000 --> 13:00.900
Why are you taking
your temperature?

13:00.960 --> 13:05.430
I think some little snot locker
gave me smallpox.

13:05.500 --> 13:08.700
(phone rings)

13:08.760 --> 13:11.530
Oh, man, leave me alone.

13:11.600 --> 13:13.530
Is that Mom?

13:13.600 --> 13:15.160
You think maybe I might want
to talk to her?

13:15.230 --> 13:16.530
Do you?

13:16.600 --> 13:18.200
Of course not.
It's the principle.

13:18.260 --> 13:21.430
Well, that wasn't Mom.
It was Herb.

13:21.500 --> 13:22.630
Why is Herb calling?

13:22.700 --> 13:24.560
Since Judith
threw him out,

13:24.630 --> 13:26.600
he wants me to help
him pick up women.

13:26.660 --> 13:29.760
Wait.
Backupbackupbackupbackup
backupbackup!

13:29.830 --> 13:32.230
Wait. Judith threw Herb out?
When?

13:32.300 --> 13:35.030
I don't know.
Apparently, about a week ago.

13:35.100 --> 13:36.930
Oh, my God.

13:37.000 --> 13:38.830
That's terrible.

13:38.900 --> 13:41.460
<i>Judith must be
devastated.</i>

13:47.060 --> 13:47.900
Alan.

13:47.960 --> 13:48.960
Yeah?

13:49.030 --> 13:50.800
You got a little evil
on your face.

13:52.800 --> 13:54.000
Other side.

13:56.300 --> 13:59.400
* Men. *

14:01.160 --> 14:03.430
Oh, Judith, that's terrible.

14:03.500 --> 14:05.860
You must be devastated.

14:09.160 --> 14:11.260
<i>You must be devastated.</i>

14:14.130 --> 14:15.660
What are
you doing here?

14:15.730 --> 14:16.960
Oh, I'm sorry to bother you.

14:17.030 --> 14:19.100
Apparently, Jake left
his Social Studies book,

14:19.160 --> 14:20.160
so here I am.

14:20.230 --> 14:22.260
I think I saw it
in the bathroom.

14:22.330 --> 14:24.660
Why?
Was he out of toilet paper?

14:27.460 --> 14:31.300
Wouldn't it be great
if he could learn that way?

14:31.360 --> 14:34.160
You know, assmosis.

14:35.200 --> 14:36.260
What?

